body_html:
Thanks for your quick reply.

GCC is 4.2.1 in Mac, while tensorflow works well without any warning on ubuntu (GCC 5.4.0). Hence I guess that these warnings are related to gcc version.

It seems that many people try to update gcc, while most get in trouble, see #336, #75, #649.

In all, if tensorflow supports to compile with the default compiler on Mac (or more detailed Instruction about how to test on Mac for developer), life will be easy.
